tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal tissues displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity with a dot-like or granular pattern. Pneumocytes, bile ducts, glial cells and muscle cells were weakly stained or negative.
Malignant cells displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity with a dot-like or granular pattern.

Most normal tissues displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity, often with a granular pattern. Renal glomeruli, oral mucosa, bile ducts, pneumocytes, glial cells, smooth muscle cells and cells in white pulp of spleen were weakly stained or negative.

Moderate granular or dot like cytoplasmic positivity was observed in most malignant cells. A few cases of non-Hodgkin's lymphomas, prostate and endometrial cancers were strongly stained. Several cases of squamous and basal cell carcinomas were weakly stained or negative.
